Beginning Saturday Sept. 12 through Sunday Sept. 20: Crews will close all lanes of the northbound span of the Interstate Bridge around-the-clock while they replace mechanical parts that help raise and lower the bridge. During the 9-day closure northbound and southbound traffic will share the three lanes and sidewalk on the southbound span. The sidewalk on the southbound span will remain open at all times for people walking or riding bicycles. During the bridge closure four ramps in the project area will close for traffic control and to ensure a safe work zone. Signs will direct travelers to detour routes.Marine Drive on-ramp to I-5 north in Portland.Hayden Island on-ramp to I-5 north in Portland.Northbound I-5 off-ramp to SR 14 in Vancouver.SR 14/Washington Street on-ramp to southbound I-5 in Vancouver.
